snippet.textDisplay: The game looks so great but I'm just worried about one thing though. All those action-filled scenes from the trailers and emphasizing on nemesis "chasing" you instead of stalking you (unlike Mr.X from re2 or Jack Baker from Re7) make me wonder if Capcom redid their mistake of turning resident evil games from survival-horror games, filled with uncertainty, to more action-packed "cat and mouse" game. Because honestly, getting chased around by a human killing machine is scary and all, but being stalked (or not even knowing if you are) and playing hide and seek with it while feeling totally powerless is far more scary. Not to mention that feeling of uncertainty and not being sure what to do or where to go is what made re2, re7, outlast and many other, again, "survival" horror games so great. I just hope they manage to keep the player always unsure and scared rather than just constantly running from nemesis or shooting through hordes of zombies as Carlos.
snippet.textOriginal: The game looks so great but I'm just worried about one thing though. All those action-filled scenes from the trailers and emphasizing on nemesis "chasing" you instead of stalking you (unlike Mr.X from re2 or Jack Baker from Re7) make me wonder if Capcom redid their mistake of turning resident evil games from survival-horror games, filled with uncertainty, to more action-packed "cat and mouse" game. Because honestly, getting chased around by a human killing machine is scary and all, but being stalked (or not even knowing if you are) and playing hide and seek with it while feeling totally powerless is far more scary. Not to mention that feeling of uncertainty and not being sure what to do or where to go is what made re2, re7, outlast and many other, again, "survival" horror games so great. I just hope they manage to keep the player always unsure and scared rather than just constantly running from nemesis or shooting through hordes of zombies as Carlos.

snippet.textDisplay: Cara que lerda foi essa aí, não é possível que ninguém percebeu que fizeram uma montagem com a arma do Nemesis com um dos Bosses do MGS1 com aquele barril nas costas, a arma do Nemesis sempre foi uma Bazooka o cara agora aparece com um túnel nas costas e um lança chamas, aff..tem que inovar tem mais da uma liberdade de movimentação ao personagem que não tinha antes já que se trata de um zumbi inteligente. 🤷🏻‍♂️ Outra coisa que não entendi, o Carlos Oliveira sempre foi um soldado jovem o cara (Militar) aparece com um cabelo enorme uma barba asquerosa, em quanto o Nicolai vem todo no padrão, moda é uma merda quer invadir tudo tbm...Bom pra quem só quer joga tá bom. Fica quieta se não aparece o público que ferrou com os games....FF
